column39: SINGLE SCHMITT-TRIGGER BUFFER This single Schmitt-trigger buffer is designed for 1.65-V to 5.5-V VCC operation. The SN74LVC1G17-Q1 contains one buffer and performs the Boolean function Y = A. The device functions as an independent buffer, but because of Schmitt action, it may have different input threshold levels for positive-going (VT+) and negative-going (VT–) signals.
